[SN]TITLE[SN]
Co Antrim Shield: Ballymena start defence against Welders

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Ballymena United will begin their bid to retain the Co Antrim Shield with a home game against Championship side H&W Welders on 20 September.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
United won last season's final by beating Linfield, who host Donegal Celtic in the first round.
Crusaders make the trip to Larne, Cliftonville host Bangor and Glentoran are away to Ballyclare Comrades.
Ards will take on Knockbreda, Carrick Rangers welcome PSNI and Newington YC face Albert Foundry.
Ballymena edged out Linfield 3-2 in a thrilling Shield final at Windsor Park in January.
Goals from Paddy McNally, David Cushley and Eoin Kane gave the Showgrounds side their sixth success in the competition.
